text: Burikazganovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Burikazganovsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 799 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 18 km from Sterlitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Burikazganovo
